A Kitale court has released businessman ken Muyundo, on a 200,000 shilling cash bail after he denied attempted murder charges. Muyundo is accused of allegedly shooting and wounding Phanice Chemutai Juma on July 8th, at Kiminini market in the county of Trans Nzoia. Appearing for the suspect, criminal lawyer Cliff Ombeta requested the court to release the accused on bond, citing that his client was unwell and needed to seek medical attention. And as ktn&rsquo;s Elvis Kosgei now reports, this comes as the manhunt for fugitive police officer caroline Kangogo continues as she remains the key suspect in the murder of two men.